name: Greenbumi Cafe
address: Jl. Gulingan, Mengwitani, Kec. Mengwi, Kab. Badung, Mengwitani, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1:
Nice little spot surrounded by green rice fields and a beautiful view of the sunset. There is a kid's swing and small climbing frame so it's good for families too, with kids options on the menu.
They serve Indonesian and Western staples (e.g. nasi goreng, tipat cantok, spaghetti & pizza etc)
Very reasonably priced. I wish the chairs were more comfortable as it's a relaxing place to come for a bite but the seats are too hard!
review 2: I was here a couple of years ago and now I'm back again.  I was very hungry, I made food quickly.  Everything was delicious and inexpensive.  I'll be back again for sure
review 3: Excellent place after you have visited some temples around. The staff is super friendly and smiling. The prices are reasonable and the food and drinks came fast. The ambiance is ni e and they have a pretty cool pond of koi fish. The fish (nyat-nyat) was delicious!
review 4:
We are fans of Green Kubu and found out that they have GreenBumi just nearby from home.
Nice cozy place.
This evening was our 6th times to dine here.
Food was good and affordable.
review 5: A very nice place, the scenery around is beautiful and natural, instagramable. Reasonable prices.
